    "Body": " Sr. Information Systems Engineer Transaction Network Services - 3.3 Reston, VA Apply Now Job Details Full-timeEstimated: $120,000 - $160,000 a year Benefits 401(k) Full Job Description This position will be responsible for designing, planning, installing, maintaining, and troubleshooting telecom applications and services offered by the Telecom Services Division of TNS. In this role, the Systems Engineer will have a wide range of responsibilities and will work with development, product management, network operations, and external customers to plan, deploy, and manage systems and services encompassing mobile data roaming, number portability, VoIP, IP & SS7 signaling, and robocall solutions. Primary Duties and Responsibilities: Design, plan, install, administer, and troubleshoot high-availability systems, applications, and services in production and lab/test environments. Analyze and resolve complex problems including packet-level interoperability issues. Support, maintain, and enhance systems. Plan for system growth. Establish performance measurements for systems, analyze problems, make recommendations for improvements, and implement tuning adjustments. Analyze recovery scenarios. Direct, conduct, and participate in architecture/design review, requirements analysis, and capacity planning. Provide guidance to development and product management teams. Provide expert consultation and specialized analysis to develop solutions and deploy services for customers. Partner and work with internal teams to initiate process and procedure improvements. Lead the integration of applications and services with network management tools and other enterprise tools. Develop KPIs and SLIs for capacity planning, performance management, monitoring, and reporting. Oversee daily operations of large-scale carrier grade systems. Schedule, document and implement maintenance and troubleshooting procedures as necessary. Pro-actively communicate status to management and customers. Mentor, train, and provide technical guidance to team engineers. Qualifications 8+ years of experience in planning, integrating, and operating carrier or enterprise-grade high-availability solutions. Expertise in Linux system administration. Experience with Virtualization solutions such as VMware, OpenStack, and Docker. Deep understanding of systems and network architecture of large-scale distributed solutions. Solid scripting skills in Perl, Python, Bash or similar scripting languages. Strong understanding and working knowledge of IP networks and security devices including routers, switches, load balancers, and firewalls. Experience with the administration and implementation of monitoring, analytics, and network management tools such as Nagios and Splunk. Self-starter mentality with the ability to initiate and manage multiple projects with minimal direction. Exceptional customer service, leadership, organizational, communication and interface skills. Understanding of project management methodologies and practices. Demonstrated problem solving and incident management skills. Willingness to participate in an on-call rotation with 24x7x365 availability as needed. Willingness to travel occasionally (< than 10%). Optional Desired Qualifications: Experience with Ansible, Chef, Puppet, or other automation frameworks. Knowledge of Agile methodology and DevOps practices. Experience with telecom services and protocols. Understanding of security and compliance requirements such as SOX and PCI. Education and Certifications: Bachelor's degree in Computer Science or a related field, or equivalent work experience We have been delivering industry-leading solutions for the payments, financial and telecommunications industries since 1990. We are the preferred supplier of networking, integrated data and voice services to many leading organizations in the global payments and financial communities, as well as a provider of extensive telecommunications network solutions to service providers. We are a privately held company with a healthy balance sheet, secure assets and a loyal customer base that includes some of the largest global blue-chip companies in the world. Many of the world\u2019s leading companies continue to count on us as their primary provider of a range of networking and communication services, enabling them to expand regionally, nationally and globally. We provide services to customers in over 60 countries throughout the world. We manage some of the largest real-time community networks in the world, enabling industry participants to simply and securely interact and transact with other businesses, to access the data and applications they need, over managed and secure communications platforms. Our existing footprint supports millions of connections and provide access to critical databases. Our network securely blends private and public networking to enable customers to utilize a single connection for \"one-to-many\" and \"many-to-many\"connections over a global platform. Since our launch we have helped our customers and communities of interest, requiring secure and reliable communications solutions, to evolve from legacy to leading-edge technologies. Today the company provides a full range of services from dedicated connections to managed IP network solutions, providing local support and global reach to medium and large enterprises and service providers. Application Instructions Applicants are encouraged to submit an electronic resume when applying for our positions. Job postings are open until filled, unless otherwise specified. "
